This paper deals with clustering algorithms that rely on human computation, which is a common theme in the sub-category of Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC). However, the paper also focuses on machine learning techniques for clustering, which suggests that it may belong to the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of algorithms for approximation and optimization, which are common themes in the sub-categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper deals with the analysis of data, which is a common theme in the sub-category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI).
